Instructions
 Create a ZIP file and GitHub repository having the name StudentID_COMP3123-exec04.zip. Also, upload screenshots showing output or any errors.

Create an express JS application having the name StudentID_COMP3123-exec04
Submit the GitHub repo link
Add the express framework and nodemon to package.json
Create a route for the following endpoints 
A GET request to /hello that returns "Hello Express JS".
A GET request to /user with query parameters for firstname and lastname.
A POST request to /user with path parameters for firstname and lastname.
Explanation:
GET /hello:

Returns "Hello Express JS" as plain text.
GET /user:

This uses query string parameters (?firstname=value&lastname=value). If the parameters are not provided, it defaults to "Pritesh" and "Patel".
Example: GET /user?firstname=John&lastname=Doe returns {"firstname":"John","lastname":"Doe"}.
POST /user:

This expects path parameters for firstname and lastname.
Example: POST /user/John/Doe returns {"firstname":"John","lastname":"Doe"}.